has a wide Indo-Pacific distribution although, like some species with such a large range, it has a consistently different colour form in the Pacific: a band of white dots is present around the margin and there is dense white pigmentation on the gills (
<bibRefCitation author="Carlson, CH" journalOrPublisher="The Veliger" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" pagination="16 - 24" title="Three new Halgerda species (Doridoidea: Nudibranchia: Opisthobranchia) from Guam." volume="36" year="1993">Carlson and Hoff 1993</bibRefCitation>
; Yonow in prep.).
</paragraph>
